---
import { Box, Button, Card, Flex, Grid, Heading, Quote, Section, Text, Em, Strong } from '@radix-ui/themes';
import { ArrowTopRightIcon, GitHubLogoIcon } from '@radix-ui/react-icons';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import "@radix-ui/themes/styles.css";
---

<Layout>
    <Section
        py={{ initial: "9" }}
        px={{ initial: "5" }}
        height="100%"
    >
        <Flex direction="column" justify="center" align="center" gap={{ initial: "5", sm: "9" }} width={{ initial: "100%" }} height={{ initial: "100%" }}>
            <Flex direction="column" justify="center" align="center" gap={{ initial: "2", sm: "3" }} width={{ initial: "100%" }}>
                <Heading size={{ initial: "8", xs: "9" }} align="center" wrap="balance">
                    Lightweight<br />Comments<br />Made Simple
                </Heading>
                <Text size={{ initial: "3", xs: "5" }} align="center" color="gray">
                    Add functional and safe comments to your website or application with ease.
                </Text>
            </Flex>
            <Flex direction={{ initial: "column", sm: "row" }} gap={{ initial: "3", xs: "2" }}>
                <a href="https://docs.kommentar.dev" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">
                    <Button variant="classic" size={{ initial: "3", xs: "4" }} style={{ cursor: "pointer" }}>
                        Start Self Hosting
                        <ArrowTopRightIcon />
                    </Button>
                </a>
                <a href="https://github.com/kommentar/kommentar" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">
                    <Button variant="soft" size={{ initial: "3", xs: "4" }} style={{ cursor: "pointer" }}>
                        View on GitHub
                        <GitHubLogoIcon />
                    </Button>
                </a>
            </Flex>
        </Flex>
    </Section>

    <Section
        id="features"
        py={{ initial: "9" }}
        px={{ initial: "5" }}
        height="25%"
    >
        <Flex direction="column" justify="center" align="center" gap={{ initial: "3", sm: "4" }} width={{ initial: "100%" }} height={{ initial: "100%" }}>
            <Heading size={{ initial: "8", xs: "9" }} align="center" wrap="balance">
                Features
            </Heading>
            <Text size={{ initial: "3", xs: "5" }} align="center" color="gray">
                Everything you need for a functional commenting system, without the complexity.
            </Text>
            <Grid columns={{ initial: "1", sm: "2" }} gap="3" width="100%" mt={{ initial: "4" }}>
                <Box>
                    <Card>
                        <Flex direction="column" gap={{ initial: "2"}} p={{ initial: "3" }}>
                            <Heading size="4" color="orange">Self Hostable</Heading>
                            <Text>
                                Self-hosted solution means your data stays on your servers. No third-party tracking with full control.
                            </Text>
                        </Flex>
                    </Card>
                </Box>
                <Box>
                    <Card>
                        <Flex direction="column" gap={{ initial: "2"}} p={{ initial: "3" }}>
                            <Heading size="4" color="orange">Open Source</Heading>
                            <Text>
                                Fully open source code means you can review everything and be sure nothing funky is going on.
                            </Text>
                        </Flex>
                    </Card>
                </Box>
                <Box>
                    <Card>
                        <Flex direction="column" gap={{ initial: "2"}} p={{ initial: "3" }}>
                            <Heading size="4" color="orange">Smart Filters</Heading>
                            <Text>
                                Smart profanity filters via <a href="https://www.profanity.dev" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">profanity.dev</a>
                                to prevent toxic content. An in-house solution is in the works!
                            </Text>
                        </Flex>
                    </Card>
                </Box>
                <Box>
                    <Card>
                        <Flex direction="column" gap={{ initial: "2"}} p={{ initial: "3" }}>
                            <Heading size="4" color="orange">Unstyled Components</Heading>
                            <Text>
                                Components to help you get going with as less friction as possible.
                                Not available yet, but coming soon!
                            </Text>
                        </Flex>
                    </Card>
                </Box>
            </Grid>
        </Flex>
    </Section>

    <Section
        id="faq"
        py={{ initial: "9" }}
        px={{ initial: "5" }}
        height="25%"
    >
        <Flex direction="column" justify="center" align="center" gap={{ initial: "3", sm: "4" }} width={{ initial: "100%" }} height={{ initial: "100%" }}>
            <Heading size={{ initial: "8", xs: "9" }} align="center" wrap="balance">
                Frequently Asked Questions (I think)
            </Heading>

            <Flex direction="column" gap="6" justify="center" width={{ initial: "100%", sm: "50%" }}>
                <Flex direction="column" justify="start" width="100%" mt={{ initial: "6" }}>
                    <Text color="orange"><Strong><Quote>How good is Kommentar?</Quote></Strong></Text>
                    <Text>
                        I built Kommentar for myself.
                        It gets the job done for me.
                        The rest is for you to decide!
                        Feel free to <a href="https://github.com/kommentar/kommentar/issues" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">request a feature on Github</a> üòÅ
                    </Text>
                </Flex>

                <Flex direction="column" justify="start" width="100%">
                    <Text color="orange"><Strong><Quote>Why did you build Kommentar?</Quote></Strong></Text>
                    <Text>
                        I have a personal site over at <a href="https://safwanyp.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">safwanyp.com</a>
                        where I <Em>try</Em> to write stuff. The last time I made a post, someone told me they would have loved if there was a comments
                        section. That's what motivated me to build Kommentar.
                    </Text>
                </Flex>

                <Flex direction="column" justify="start" width="100%">
                    <Text color="orange"><Strong><Quote>What does Kommentar mean?</Quote></Strong></Text>
                    <Text>
                        Kommentar is a Swedish word that means "Comments". I used that word simply because I'm trying to learn Swedish, and it sounded nice!
                    </Text>
                </Flex>

                <Flex direction="column" justify="start" width="100%">
                    <Text color="orange"><Strong><Quote>Why is the only option to Self-Host?</Quote></Strong></Text>
                    <Text>
                        Like I mentioned before, I built Kommentar for myself.
                        I have been trying to get into self hosting everything I use regularly, which made me realize how
                        nice it is to always have the option to self-host a particular service/application.<br /><br />
                        On top of that, I am just one guy and don't see the need to provide a managed solution until
                        there is an actual demand or need for it.
                    </Text>
                </Flex>

                <Flex direction="column" justify="start" width="100%">
                    <Text color="orange"><Strong><Quote>Will there be a managed/SaaS offering of Kommentar?</Quote></Strong></Text>
                    <Text>
                        For now, no. But if enough people ask for it then I will consider it!
                    </Text>
                </Flex>

                <Flex direction="column" justify="start" width="100%">
                    <Text color="orange"><Strong><Quote>How can I support?</Quote></Strong></Text>
                    <Text>
                        If you really are wondering about this, thanks a lot!
                        The easiest way is to tell other people about Kommentar,
                        and to drop a ‚òÖ on the <a href="https://github.com/kommentar/kommentar" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">main Kommentar repository</a>.
                    </Text>
                </Flex>
            </Flex>
        </Flex>
    </Section>
</Layout>
